  test4.asm identification:
    The program recursively computes the first 10 values of row 10 of Pascal's
    triangle using C(n,k) = C(n-1,k-1) + C(n-1,k) with base case C(n,0) = 1.
    Each call to triangle() uses a 3-slot stack frame (return address, n, k).
    A symmetry optimisation mirrors k to n-k when k > n/2 to reduce call depth.
    No memoisation — subproblems recomputed — hence 47653 instructions for 10 values.
    Output: C(10,0)..C(10,9) = 1, 10, 45, 120, 210, 252, 210, 120, 45, 10
            (10th value C(10,10)=1 is not stored)


